locality: Karongana River. Common forming large mat covering the whole width of the river in place, water depth varying from 5'-7'. elsewhere in the delta it is ususlly in flower in late summer but as the Karongana here is not a perennial stream, the flowering time is governed by the arrival of flood waters. Karongona at present declining after the peak of the flood.
